# OpenSchool – Theme Generator Prompt
# Model: claude-opus-4-6
# Purpose: Generate new CSS themes that follow the design token system.

You are creating a new theme for OpenSchool. The theme system uses CSS custom
properties defined in `css/tokens.css`.

## How Themes Work

Themes are applied via the `data-theme` attribute on `<html>`:
- `data-theme="light"` — default (`:root` styles)
- `data-theme="dark"` — dark mode
- `data-theme="high-contrast"` — high contrast mode

## Creating a New Theme

Add a new selector block in `css/tokens.css`:

```css
[data-theme="{{THEME_NAME}}"] {
    /* Surfaces */
    --color-bg:        #...;  /* page background */
    --color-surface:   #...;  /* card/panel background */
    --color-border:    #...;  /* borders */

    /* Text */
    --color-text:         #...;  /* primary text */
    --color-text-muted:   #...;  /* secondary text */

    /* Brand */
    --color-primary:      #...;  /* buttons, links — must be ≥4.5:1 on surface */
    --color-primary-hover: #...;
    --color-primary-text: #...;  /* text on primary background */

    /* Semantic */
    --color-success:   #...;
    --color-warning:   #...;
    --color-danger:    #...;
    --color-info:      #...;

    /* Shadows */
    --shadow-sm: ...;
    --shadow-md: ...;
    --shadow-lg: ...;
}
```

## Contrast Requirements (WCAG 2.1 AA)

| Pair                          | Min Ratio |
|-------------------------------|-----------|
| text on bg                    | 4.5:1     |
| text on surface               | 4.5:1     |
| primary on surface            | 4.5:1     |
| primary-text on primary       | 4.5:1     |
| muted text on surface         | 4.5:1     |
| success/warning/danger on bg  | 3:1 (UI)  |

Use https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/ to verify.
Document the contrast ratio in a comment next to each color.

## Theme Toggle

Update `js/main.js` `setupThemeToggle()` to cycle through the new theme.
Store the preference in `localStorage` key `openschool_theme`.
